      "source": "The Org (Decart profile)",
      "url": "https://theorg.com/org/decart/org-chart/michael-zimmerman",
      "summary": "Michael Zimmerman currently serves in the Office of the CTO at Google, with a focus on agents and digital workforce technologies since February 2025. Before joining Google, he was involved with generative AI and life sciences startups between 2022 and 2024, serving in executive and advisory roles including board member, investor, acting CEO, and advisor. Zimmerman's previous executive roles include CEO positions at DeepCube and Bitfusion—both of which were acquired—as well as General Manager at Marvell Semiconductor. He has also held leadership positions at Tilera Corporation and Annapurna Labs, contributing in networking and compute. Academically, he completed executive education at Stanford and holds degrees in computer science and engineering from Nova Southeastern University and Tel Aviv University."
    },
    {
      "source": "The Org (Speedata profile)",
      "url": "https://theorg.com/org/speedata/org-chart/michael-zimmerman",
      "summary": "Michael Zimmerman holds a position in Google Cloud's Office of the CTO, focusing on Agents & Digital Workforce since February 2025. Prior to this, he worked with generative AI and life sciences startups in various leadership and advisory capacities from 2022 to 2024. His earlier roles include executive experience in LLMops and MLOps at cnvrg.io, being CEO of both DeepCube and Bitfusion, and general management at Marvell Semiconductor. Notably, he led Tilera Corporation as Vice President, defining the industry's first SmartNIC technology. His education includes an executive program at Stanford, a master's in computer science from Nova Southeastern University, and dual degrees in computer engineering and an MBA from Tel Aviv University."
    },
    {
      "source": "Google Cloud (Office of the CTO blog)",
      "url": "https://cloud.google.com/transform/ask-octo-making-sense-of-agents",
      "summary": "Michael Zimmerman is a Principal Engineer in Google Cloud's Office of the CTO. He is an expert in agent-based systems, working alongside a team of technical experts and former CTOs to support Google's largest and most strategic customers in addressing complex tech challenges. Zimmerman contributes thought leadership on building and scaling intelligent AI agent systems, advising enterprises on how to practically integrate agents into their technology stacks."
    },
    {
      "source": "Luma (AI Tech Leaders' Club event page)",
      "url": "https://luma.com/mq1948jl",
      "summary": "Michael Zimmerman is listed as a confirmed speaker representing the Office of the CTO at Google Cloud for an executive event focused on enterprise AI and operational efficiency. He is described as a product and technology leader specializing in generative AI and enterprise platforms, indicating recognition in the field by peer AI and product leadership communities."
    }
  ]
}
